=Definition=


"Co-operative economics is a field of economics, socialist economics, and political economy, which is concerned with co-operatives. Notable theoreticians who have contributed to the field include Charles Gide, Robert Owen, Beatrice and Sydney Webb, J.T.W. Mitchell, Paul Lambart, Race Mathews, David Griffiths, and G.D.H. Cole."
(http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Co-operative_economics)


